  "text": "Found 12 C++ source files in sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2 under source/common/tls/ and source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/ containing TLS certificate verification logic. The verification chain works as follows: (1) ContextImpl::customVerifyCallback (context_impl.cc) is the BoringSSL callback entry point registered via SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify with verify_mode. (2) It delegates to CertValidator::doVerifyCertChain (cert_validator.h abstract interface). (3) DefaultCertValidator (default_validator.cc) is the primary implementation: it calls X509_verify_cert for cert chain verification and SSL_CTX_set_verify in addClientValidationContext for server-side client cert validation. (4) SPIFFEValidator (spiffe_validator.cc) is the alternative implementation for SPIFFE workload identity, also calling X509_verify_cert. Server-side client cert validation: server_context_impl.cc delegates to addClientValidationContext which calls SSL_CTX_set_verify(ctx, SSL_VERIFY_PEER | SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT). Client-side server cert validation: client_context_impl.cc uses SSL_set_verify per-connection when SAN overrides are present; main path goes through customVerifyCallback -> doVerifyCertChain -> X509_verify_cert. Validation status tracking is in ssl_handshaker.h/cc (setCertificateValidationStatus, certificateValidationResult). Error reporting uses Utility::getX509VerificationErrorInfo in utility.cc.",
